  "text": "Finally ǫ noise , finite in the thermodynamic limit, is a small parameter of the theory and we limit ourselves in general to first order in this quantity. An exception is made in subsection II B where expressions to all orders in ǫ noise are given. Starting with the initial state (2) with φ = 0, we will show that this minimal model reproduces the scalings [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . In the subsequent sections III and IV we will detail an analogy between the dephasing model and microscopic models accounting for the effect of particle losses or of non-zero temperature on squeezing. The parameter ǫ noise introduced here (16) will then be related to the lost fraction of particles or the populations of thermally excited modes, respectively.",
